# Implementation Plan - DataToCharts Web UI

## Goal Description
Create a modern, "premium" web interface to interact with the existing CrewAI agent. The UI will allow users to upload CSV files or input text to generate Tremor chart configurations and implementation guides.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The UI will require `node.js` and `npm` to be installed for the frontend, and `fastapi` `uvicorn` `python-multipart` for the backend.
> The CrewAI agent will be executed as a library call within the FastAPI server.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (`src/`)

#### [NEW] [api.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Downloads/data_to_charts_automation_v1_crewai-project/src/data_to_charts_automation/api.py)
- FastAPI application.
- Endpoint `POST /analyze`:
    - Accepts `file: UploadFile` or `text: str`.
    - Saves uploaded file to `temp/` (if provided).
    - Initializes [DataToChartsAutomationCrew](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Downloads/data_to_charts_automation_v1_crewai-project/src/data_to_charts_automation/crew.py#17-95).
    - Calls [crew().kickoff(inputs={'data_source': ...})](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Downloads/data_to_charts_automation_v1_crewai-project/src/data_to_charts_automation/crew.py#79-89).
    - Returns the result (Markdown/JSON).
- CORS middleware to allow frontend access.

### Frontend ([ui/](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Downloads/data_to_charts_automation_v1_crewai-project/src/data_to_charts_automation/crew.py#69-77))

#### [NEW] [Vite Project](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Downloads/data_to_charts_automation_v1_crewai-project/ui/)
- Initialize using `npm create vite@latest`.
- **Tech Stack**: React, TailwindCSS, Lucide-React (icons).
- **Components**:
    - `App.jsx`: Main layout.
    - `InputSection.jsx`: Tabs for "Text Input" and "File Upload".
    - `ResultSection.jsx`: Markdown renderer for the agent output.
    - `LoadingState.jsx`: Premium loading animation (e.g., "Agents working...").

### Configuration

#### [MODIFY] [pyproject.toml](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Downloads/data_to_charts_automation_v1_crewai-project/pyproject.toml)
- Add `fastapi`, `uvicorn`, `python-multipart`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None planned for UI in this iteration (manual verification preferred for UI/UX).

### Manual Verification
1.  **Setup**:
    - `pip install fastapi uvicorn python-multipart`
    - `cd ui && npm install`
2.  **Run Backend**: `uvicorn src.data_to_charts_automation.api:app --reload`
3.  **Run Frontend**: `cd ui && npm run dev`
4.  **Test Flow**:
    - Open `http://localhost:5173`.
    - Upload a sample CSV (I will create one).
    - Click "Generate Charts".
    - Verify the loading animation appears.
    - Verify the agent logs (on backend console) and final output (on UI).
